title: Re: Favorite Comedian
content:
I enjoy Home Improvment (Tim Allen) and (Jerry) Seinfeld, but haven't really found their stand-up gear very funny (at least, what I've seen of it).

And Rodney Rude... He doesn't amuse me at all.

I don't know much work of 'classic' comedians (for lack of a better description), so I really couldn't say any of them as my favourites.--------------

title: well...
content:
A friend of mine gave me a 70mb WMV file that was heavily compressed but is about 40 minutes of a man named Russell Peters doing stand-up in Canada... really funny stuff to me, because he hit on a lot of topics which don't come up often in America.

A lot of American stand-up comedy is "black people white people" kind of stuff, or the "guys, does your wife..." kind of thing. Russell Peters, on the other hand, did a lot of funny stuff involving Indian, African, and Chinese people which I found hilarious.
